	<principle>
		<title>Coulomb's Law</title>
		<statement>
			<p>The electric field created by a point charge <m>q_{\text{source}}</m> is given by <me>\vec{E}_{pc} = \frac{kq_{\text{source}}}{r^2}\hat{r}</me>  Here <m>k = 9 \times 10^9 \frac{\text{Nm}^2}{\text{C}^2}</m> is a constant, <m>\hat{r}</m> is a unit vector that points radially outward from the location of the point charge, and <m>r</m> is the distance from the point charge to the place where the electric field is being evaluated.</p>
		</statement>
	</principle>

	<exercises>
