		<exercise>
			<p>Recall <xref ref="x_graphing-r-hat"/>, in which you made a 2D-map of a vector field.  The vector field you mapped is proportional to <m>\hat{r}</m>! Map this vector field and describe how this vector field changes (or stays the same) at different points in space.  What do you think the map would look like if you could make it three-dimensional?</p>
		</exercise>
